comments: Embiid (PHI) establishes himself in Joe's (OKC) path and marginal contact occurs as they briefly engage during the pick.
Joe (OKC) is slightly late to the spot when some contact occurs with Lowry (PHI), who is able to complete his intended pass.
Dort (OKC) legally contests Harris' (PHI) post shot attempt.
Batum (PHI) slightly extends his arms and marginal contact occurs with Holmgren (OKC) during the rebound.
Williams (OKC) does not extend backwards or deliver any illegal contact to Lowry (PHI) as Lowry runs behind him.
Embiid's (PHI) resting hand slides off Wiggins' (OKC) body and marginal contact occurs as Wiggins fades away from the basket on the shot attempt.
Williams (OKC) legally contests Embiid's (PHI) jump shot attempt.

Oubre Jr. (PHI) and Holmgren (OKC) briefly engage and immediately disengage before Holmgren loses his balance on his own. Any follow-through contact between Holmgren and Harris (PHI) after Holmgren goes to the ground is deemed incidental.
Embiid (PHI) makes clean contact with the ball on his block attempt during Dort's (OKC) shot at the basket.
Embiid (PHI) and Williams (OKC) mutually engage and immediately disengage as marginal contact occurs during the rebound.
Williams (OKC) moves forward into and initiates contact with Embiid's (PHI) body, which affects his shot attempt.
Harris (PHI) and Holmgren (OKC) engage and disengage with one another and marginal contact occurs as the screen is set.
After Giddey (OKC) loses control of his dribble, Embiid (PHI) makes clean contact with the ball and deflects it away from Giddey.

Replay review of the foul called on Holmgren (OKC) pursuant to a coach's challenge was deemed unsuccessful. Holmgren fails to establish a legal guarding position in Embiid's (PHI) path and makes contact with his body, which affects the driving shot attempt.
During the inbound, Embiid (PHI) grasps and then quickly releases Williams' (OKC) jersey as the screen is set.

During the rebound, Embiid (PHI) deflects the ball away from Giddey (OKC) and the ball goes out of bounds.  There is no clear and conclusive evidence that shows that Giddey is the last player to touch the ball before it goes out of bounds instead.
Batum (PHI) legally contests Williams' (OKC) jump shot attempt.
Lowry (PHI) and Dort (OKC) come together in pursuit of the loose ball and marginal contact occurs before Dort deflects away the rebound.

Holmgren (OKC) commits a take foul on Harris (PHI). The transition take foul rule does not apply to the last two minutes of either the fourth quarter or overtime. After review, it is determined that there are 0.9 seconds left on the game clock when the foul occurs.
